description:
Colin King: sophisticated British playboy by day, elite super-spy Ninjak by night! There's a traitor in the ranks of the Weaponeer organization and Ninjak is on his trail. But the agents of the insidious Dr. Silk and his terrorist Webnet organization are on the hunt as well - and they won't stop until they have Ninjak dead to rights!

Notes:

  • 1st appearance of Fitzhugh.

Covers:

  • Regular
  • Chromium
name: Black Water Part 1

description: Webnet's "Black Water" cold fusion technology threatens to drown Ninjak on dry land! Can he escape in time? And even if he does, with every remaining agent of Weaponeer now dead, he'll have to go it alone during his final showdown with Dr. Silk! raitor in the ranks of the Weaponeer organization and Ninjak is on his trail. But the agents of the insidious Dr. Silk and his terrorist Webnet organization are on the hunt as well - and they won't stop until they have Ninjak dead to rights!
name: Black Water Part 2: Deluge

description:
Ninjak is recruited by the crown for a mission to Japan! But it's not until he learns that his childhood sweetheart is in the hands of a powerful Yakuza crime family that he agrees to do the job. But he'll learn that it can be awfully hard to keep the past behind you when the deadly 7th Dragon reveals his true identity!

1st appearance:

- Michiko Okubo

- Senator Yusaku Okubo
name: The 7th Dragon

description: Under assault by the Yakuza, Ninjak will have to team up with his one-time rival, the 7th Dragon, to save his childhood sweetheart and keep her senator father out of harm's way. But even if he succeeds, will family honor let him win back his lost love?
name: The 7th Dragon - Part 2: Dragonslayer

description: It's the legendary first meeting of Ninjak and X-O Manowar! Word of the X-O Manowar armor and its new abilities has spread throughout the underworld of the Valiant Universe. Can Ninjak intercept a clan of ninja assassins before they capture it and seize the power of X-O Manowar?
name: Full Metal Jacket

description: Orb Industries' online databanks are being tampered with and even X-O Manowar can't track the saboteur responsible. To locate the world-class codebreaker that is bringing his company down from the inside, Aric of Dacia must turn to his new ally ? the one and only Ninjak! But can these two heroes truly trust one another...or will they battle once more?
name: Full Metal Jacket - Part 2

description:
1st appearance & death:
-  Djinn
name: Fire And Forget
Dogs Of War

description: Ninjak has been sucked into a twisted game of Russian roulette ? and the entire world hangs in the balance! Ninjak's latest target in holded up deep with a former Soviet republic, where a rogue general is threatening to unleash a devastating laser on the West and rebuild the Iron Curtain. Trapped in unfamiliar territory, can Ninjak defeat not just one crazed madman, but the entire army at his command?
name: The Little Cossak

description: Ninjak goes digging for answers when a construction crew unearths a series of catacombs beneath the Canterbury Cathedral used by the O.S.S. in Word War II. What possible clues to his fathers past and the mysterious Operation Hope and Glory will this forgotten dungeon reveal?
name: Canterbury Tales - Part One

description:
Ninjak is trapped in a medieval dungeon between a squad of Webnet killers and a team of Russian treasure hunters! Will he be able to make it out before the hidden gold of Operation Hope and Glory falls into the wrong hands?

1st appearance:

- Jonathan King
name: Canterbury Tales - Part Two: The Knight's Tale

description:
The name's Folly, Robert Folly, and he's got a job to do when the British embassy in Yemen comes under assault by Webnet. It may be Folly's mission to keep MI-6 files out of enemy hands, but it'll take Ninjak to make sure he gets out alive and the mission gets done right!

1st appearance:

- Robert Folley
name: Mad dogs and Englishmen

description:
Webnet agent Wassily Borkov is defecting and intends to auction off his secrets. Now, Ninjak and Neville Alcott will have to go undercover to make certain that British Intelligence wins the bid. But all is not as it seems as the two are lured into the lair the White Wolf!

1st appearance:

- Sabine
name: Cry Wolf

description:
It's wheels within wheels and traps within traps when a mission to recruit a Webnet traitor seems to cost Colin King his life. Or does it? All is not as it seems on this mission and it will take all of Ninjak's lethal talents when he goes sword to claw with the mysterious White Wolf!

1st appearance:

- White Wolf
name: Cry Wolf - Part 2

description:
Things get dicey for Ninjak when Arkady Borkov's corpse gets up and goes on a rampage! Can MI-6 figure out what's to blame for this zombie killing spree? And will Ninjak be able to stop Arkady before he sets loose plague of the undead?

1st appearance:

- Plague
name: Plague - Part 1

description: Arkady Borkov, son of the White Wolf, has returned to life infected with an extraordinarily virulent parahuman strain of the plague virus. It will take all of Ninjak's skills to stop Arkady before he infects half of London with an undead plague and overzealous agents from the Ministry of Defense quarantine and terminate the other half!
name: Plague - Part Two

description: It's adventure on the high seas as Ninjak goes undercover to infiltrate a mobile Webnet spying station disguised as a Norwegian factory ship. Can he maintain cover long enough to execute his plan and cripple Dr. Silk's worldwide network, or will he be discovered and lost forever in the icy North Sea?
name: Icebreaker

description: With their communications crashed and crippled by Ninjak, Webnet is left vulnerable to a two pronged strike by the forces of MI-5. Under assault from Bloodshot's brutal guns on one side and Ninjak's silent swords on the other, Dr. Silk is sure to fall... unless he strikes first!
name: Birthquake

description: Ninjak's strike deep into the heart of Webnet has left him entangled in the sadistic games of his archenemy. If he can escape the cell he's forced to share with the grief-maddened and murderous White Wolf, he'll still have Webnet's elite team of parahuman Specialists- Shrapnel, Pariah, Brick and Jack Knife- on his trail.
name: Breaking the Web Part 2: Delusions

description: At the mercy of Webnet and the villainous Dr. Silk! Ninjak's been brainwashed, his next mission: assassinate the Prime Minister. Can Bloodshot stop him in time, or will Britain's best agent become its deadliest enemy?
name: And the Fall of Webnet

description: Ninjak catches the trail of megalomaniacal madman William Michael Pendragon and his ambitious plan to destroy Japan! Is this the revival of Webnet as Ninjak fears, or the rise of a whole new menace from Britain's past?

Ninjak's next mission sends him bounding through the Brazilian rainforest after Jason Haynes, an attorney working for one of Colin King's corporate holdings. But after a string of strange kidnappings will Ninjak be able to rescue Haynes and escape himself?
name: Uncharted Territory

description: Captured and thrown into a jungle pit with Vatican intelligence agent Gabriela Ramirez by the slave trader Terence Whittingham and his army of savages, Ninjak plans their escape. But will they be able to escape before they're downed? And will they be able to discover what the plans of the man known only as the Botanist are?
name: Uncharted Territory Part 2

description: After years of searching Neville Alcott has found the man responsible for his wife's death. Now Neville needs the man brought in alive for questioning before one of the traitor's former employer's ends his life. There's only one man Neville can turn to with so much on the line -- Ninjak!
name: Killzone

description:
Colin King must travel to Rome to repay an old friend on his wedding day. But Ninjak's trip might prove to be more than he bargained for when Vatican secret agents crash the wedding!

Last issue.
name: Inner Sanctus

description:
Introducing the Guardians of Freedom - the Shogun Warriors. Massive engines of power, forged by the technology of the future, and piloted by the bravest heroes the world has ever known. In the first exciting issue Raydeen battles the colossal might of Rok-Korr! .

Note: This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Iron Man in An Irresistible Force!
name: Raydeen!

description: Worshippers of the "Black Snake" are venturing into the ancient tunnels and paths that Two-Edge once made, hoping to unlock and be heir to all of the spiritual powers that the elves and The High-Ones had ever bestowed upon the world of two moons. They must use Kullyn Kenn as their focal key in order to access and awaken these forces.
name: MINDCOIL PART 2

description:
Kullyn Kenn is being abused by a concentrated circle of apprentice psy-warriors who are followers of "the Cult of the Black Snake" (Winnowill). Jink senses this and is with #Tamia when he finds out. The two are led to Blue Mountain, where the final remnants of Winnowill's soul is joining with the ancestral dwelling place of the spirit of all elves in eternal communion with The High-Ones.

Tamia Korhat and Jink have to steal a cruiser, #659, and escape though a guardforce gives chase. Will Jink arrive in time to save her partner?
name: RIPPLES

description:
The minds from the human psy-force apprentices have been captured by the lingering presence of evil in Blue Mountain. This appears as a dragon spirit, whose force wells up like an insurgent tornado. There is a blast that erupts through the consciousness field of the planet. Plants & Animals remain unharmed, but the mental tsunami overwhelms all mental activities within humans.

After the psy-wave enters its host, it searches through the fears and incomplete identities and causes the creature to attack itself. This is the general pattern that began with the psy-teams and perpetuated through the government of Abode. Winnowill appears to be steering the course of this force. It is the evil presence known as #Mindcoil.
name: ON SHIFTING SANDS

description:
Note: the title of Jink #11 may refer to the pale greenish skin tone of an injured Jink, featured on the cover.

Aftermath of previous issue

There is a terrible Psychic Blast from a mind wave, and it reaches out into the planet's periphery. Soon, the teams running the advanced space stations turn on each other. All of the planet's channels of defense are severed for lack of human control.

Jink is confronting the truth about hersela as in a dream.
name: OF UNHOLY BLUE

description:
Jink's divine endowment is the ability to completely forget her history. She has forgotten all forms of her own identity, and this is an ability she can bestow upon any of her friends and family. This is a trait only displayed in one other ElfQuest elf by the name of Nightfall, who gives this power to her Recognised bond partner Redlance

Kullyn Kenn, despite being immensely attracted to her finally decides it is for the best that he completely separate himself from the bonds of a forbidden romance. He forgets about all of the fear-implantation, his training as a "tweak", and his romance with the elf.
name: BE FORGOT

description:
Dr. Sun and the Sphinx are now partners-in-crime! And Nova is forced to collect Powerhouse! Meanwhile, Comet is reunited with his son.

"The New Champions!"

Tensions rise between Nova, Dr. Sun, and the immensely powerful Sphinx. Plus, Crime Buster reveals to the Comet that he is his son. And, Powerhouse recounts his origin.
name: The New Champions!

description:
Two brave men and a woman have been recruited to pilot the giant robots known as the Shogun Warriors. The first of these warriors, Raydeen, battled and thought he had defeated the colossal Rok-Korr. But he soon learned that the monster had become even more powerful than before.. Now, Raydeen will be joined by Combatra and Dangard Ace, and if they fail....the world is doomed!

Note: This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, The Incredible Hulk Changes His Mind!
name: Warriors Three!

description: The appearance of twin colossal constructs known as the Harbingers of the Everlasting Winter signal the beginning of the end for humanity, unless the Earth's Mightiest Heroes and comicdom's First Family leap into the past and recover the key to the world's salvation! But can the Avengers and the FF triumph, even when they must return to the moment of their lowest ebb?!
name: The Praxis Agenda

description: The original X-Men, Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos and Magneto guest-star as the Avengers are scattered throughout the ages! The Earth's Mightiest Heroes must reassemble a missing artifact to save humanity, but Iron Man has neither his company nor his armor - and must face his greatest personal crisis once again! Meanwhile, Captain America is fighting in WWII again, and the Scarlet Witch has rejoined the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants! All is part of a master plan of one of the major players in the Marvel Universe - continuing the eight-part DOMINATION FACTOR adventure!
name: Strange Tales

description: Continuing the new Avengers/Fantastic Four adventure! The pieces begin to fall into place as Captain America, The Vision and Thor continue their missions into the past, and the architect of their misfortunes stands revealed as one of the greatest threats in the entire Marvel Universe! Guest-starring the original Human Torch, Sgt. Fury and the Howling Commandos!
name: Seeds of Change

description: It's the combustible conclusion to the DOMINATION FACTOR! Betrayed by one of their own, the Avengers and the Fantastic Four are even more Hard-pressed to stop our mystery villain and save the world! But seeds planted in the past bear odd fruit, offering our heroes one slim hope for victory!
name: The Domination Factor

description: The world has grinded to a standstill! But why? The FF and the Earth's Mightiest Heroes realize that only they can save the present, by journeying into the past! So what part does the Praxis Corporation play in our planet's plight? Who is the company's mysterious owner? And what connection does she have to one of the greatest threats to the Marvel Universe?
name: Arrival

description: The Inhumans, Namor, Dr. Strange and Adam Warlock guest-star as the Fantastic Four tumble through time! Scattered throughout the eons, the only way for the FF to restart time is by gathering together the pieces of the scattered artifact! Cast into the bodies of their past selves, the Thing, Mr. Fantastic, Invisible Woman and the Human Torch must first deal with the Frightful Four, the fighting-mad Inhumans, the birth of Adam Warlock and the power of the Sub-Mariner! And waiting in the wings is an even greater menace!
name: Flashback Times Four

description: Trapped in four different time periods, and with the future of all humanity at stake, will the fabulous Fantastic Four be forced to commit murder?! The enchanted fragments that they seek are there for the taking, but will comics' first family take a life to possess them? Guest-starring Dr. Strange and the Inhumans!
name: When Shatters Reality!!

description: Concluding the Avengers/Fantastic Four crossover event! Trapped as bodiless spectres in a now-remade present, the Avengers and the Fantastic Four must locate and possess their alternate selves before they can even begin to face the power of our mystery villain!
name: Yesterday's Tomorrows

description: A gamma-ray powered serial killer is plaguing Manhattan. Doc Samson, She-Hulk, and the Hulk, all gamma-powered heroes, try to stop the crimes. Polaris, a magnetic heroine, shows up.
name: Greenness Envy

description: The She-Hulk fights the real killer while Samson proves the innocence of another person who had been framed for the crimes. He acquires a sidekick nicknamed 'Geiger', who can detect gamma radiation.
name: Body Double

description: The Punisher shows up in the hunt for the killer while She-Hulk recovers from last issue. Samson tries more costume changes.
Polaris assists the heroes as they stumble upon the identity of the real killer.
name: The Final Analysis

description: Written by Paul Pope Art and cover by Pope. THB's Paul Pope (HEAVY LIQUID, 100%) goes it alone in SOLO #3! Pope begins with an ancient Greek myth, then re-imagines the classic origin of Omac and shares a personal tale. Pope also presents a slice of the Big Apple and concludes with "Teenage Sidekick," in which a captured Dick Grayson, as Robin, must struggle to escape the Joker!

The Sphinx and Dr. Sun butt heads on their journey to Xandar! Will another villain attempt to break up this new partnership?

Tensions rise as the uneasy allies hurtle through outer space toward their destination. Nova, Powerhouse, Crime-Buster, Comet, Diamondhead, and the powerful Sphinx are attacked by an armada of Skrull warships. But these champions will not be denied. Though this is the final issue in Nova's own series his story is not done yet. Nova's epic saga continues in Fantastic Four (1st Series) ##206-209 and concludes in Rom (1979) #24.
name: Invasion of the body changers!

description:
Mystique can be anything you want her to be- In a world of intrigue and seduction, where mutants are feared and hated and the are not enough to protect them, Mystique uses her shape-shifting abilities to further her own mutant rights agenda. And to get want she wants, she's not afraid to do whatever's necessary.

Mystique's true motives are put to the test in this brand new beginning for the mutant chameleon.
name: Dead Drop Gorgeous, Part 1

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Mystique is rescued from being executed by Charles Xavier and Forge and taken to New York City. The next morning Xavier and Forge explain to Mystique that she will now work as their spy for black bag missions Xavier needs done but can't involve the X-Men with. They let Mystique know if she doesn't comply they will turn her over to the authorities which means she will be executed. Mystique agrees to the deal having no choice and her first mission takes her to Cuba.
name: Drop Dead Gorgeous, Part 3

description: Mystique's new assignment from Xavier is to track down a possible new biological weapon: mutant anthrax that spreads telepathically. But Mystique is getting restless following Xavier's orders… and he might not be the only boss she's working for these days…
name: Tinker, Tailor, Mutant, Spy, Part 1

description: Mystique continues her mission to find and destroy a deadly new strain of smallpox ... but she's not the only mutant who wants to get her hands on this potentially apocalyptic bio-weapon! [This is a resolicitation, all previous orders are cancelled].
name: Tinker, Tailor, Mutant, Spy, Part 2

description: Mystique is on the trail of a woman who is a walking plague… and who has stolen a deadly biological weapon!
name: Tinker, Tailor, Mutant, Spy Part 3

description: Mystique must save humanity from a deadly, mutated form of smallpox… but will she have to sacrifice the life of her loyal field handler, Shortpack, for the greater good?
name: Tinker, Tailor, Mutant, Spy Part 4

description: Mystique’s a shape-shifting super-spy that can  literally change her skin. Forge is the mutant inventor who’s gotten under her skin. Learn more about their past and present relationship as and find out how the Maker left his mark!!!
name: Maker's Mark: Part 1

description: Overview Mystique’s globetrotting missions take her everywhere imaginable, but now she’s going back to the last place she’d ever imagine... her romantic past. Her old flame Forge can fix almost anything, but can he fix their relationship?
name: Maker's Mark: Part 2

description: Shape-shifting super-spy Mystique has a secret, and so does her tiny field handler, Shortpack. Will these two mutants be able to protect the skeletons in their closets AND help each other survive a death-defying mission?
name: Nevermore

description: When Mystique is sent to Europe to investigate a biotech company rumored to be using mutants as guinea pigs, she discovers a mystery far greater than anything she'd imagined! Join the new X-MEN: RELOAD creative team of SEAN McKEEVER (SENTINEL, The Waiting Place) and returning artist MANUEL GARCIA (AVENGERS) for this bold new adventure featuring everyone's favorite shape-shifting secret agent!
name: Unnatural, Part 1

description: When Mystique is sent to Europe to investigate a biotech company rumored to be using mutants as guinea pigs, she discovers a mystery far greater than anything she'd imagined! Join the new X-MEN: RELOAD creative team of SEAN McKEEVER (SENTINEL, The Waiting Place) and returning artist MANUEL GARCIA (AVENGERS) for this bold new adventure featuring everyone's favorite shape-shifting secret agent!
name: Unnatural, Part 2

description: As Mystique and Shortpack get closer to their objective, they must confront a new revelation: that someone is selling transient mutants as guinea pigs, slaves and worse! Will Mystique go after this mutant-selling scum, or will she allow her personal crisis to tear her apart first?
name: Unnatural, Part 3

description: It's Shortpack to the rescue in Prague when Mystique is presumed amnesiac or dead at the hands of Viktor, an unscrupulous mutant who sells other mutants on the black market!
name: Unnatural, Part 4

description: The stunning conclusion to the new ReLoad team's first action-packed tale! Mystique and Shortpack's relationship continues to strain as they work to take down DermaFree and rescue the mutant guinea pigs from execution! Shortpack comes to a decision about his future with Xavier, and Mystique is faced with a mind-numbing choice.
name: Unnatural, Part 5

description: When an assassin's bullet aims for Mystique, the shape-shifting mutant and her enigmatic employer, Shepard, hunt down the source. This issue serves as a jumping-on point and a bridge between last month's "Unnatural" arc and next month's status-quo-shattering event!
name: Ingression

description: This is it! The Quiet Man's identity is finally revealed in this series-shifting, mind-bending first part of a new arc! Mystique is sent on a mission to find Shortpack, who has mysteriously vanished. But Mystique has enough on her mind.
name: Quiet, Part 1

description: Mystique is caught between two masters—one, mutant activist Charles Xavier; the other, the mysterious Quiet Man. Now, the time has come when she can no longer serve both!
name: Quiet, Part 2

description: Can Mystique really go through with her murderous mission? Her decision might just surprise ya!
name: Quiet, Part 3

description: Choosing to take on Professor Xavier may not have been a wise choice for Mystique…especially since the X-Men are now coming after her with all chambers loaded!
name: Quiet, Part 4

description: The shocking series finale! Everything has been leading up to the explosive events of this issue! Big changes are in store for the shifty shapechanger. Miss this issue at your peril!
name: Quiet, Part 5

description: The Establishment is witness to end of the Wildstorm Universe as in shown in Wildstorm Spotlight the Big Chill in which Mr. Majestic and lonely group of survivor called the Last Ones survive the end of the universe and with the help of a godly Spartan they recreate the universe however someone is trying to control this events so that they would be the God of this new world...can the heroes possible stop this madness before it too late?

When an ancient force for evil awakens after centuries of lying in wait, the Shogun Warriors are called upon to defend mankind. But, can even the mighty Raydeen, Combatra and Dangard Ace, hope to defeat the monstrous power of the Elements of Destruction?!

Note: This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Spider-Man "Puts Himself in the Picture!"
name: Elements Of Destruction

description:
The final phase of the Shogun Warriors’ training begins as new powers are revealed and a new menace arrives to threaten mankind.

Note: This issue contains the Hostess Superhero Ad, Iron Man in Brains Over Brawn!
name: The Mech-Monster

description: Reprints of Blue Beetle (1967) #3
